From: Bedrock <bedrock@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] x86/mm: Make flush_tlb_fix_spurious_fault actually flush

On x86, flush_tlb_fix_spurious_fault() is a no-op. For deterministic
execution under hypervisors, make it actually call flush_tlb_page()
to eliminate spurious fault handling non-determinism.

Signed-off-by: Bedrock <bedrock@example.com>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable.h | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable.h b/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable.h
index abcdef123..1234567ab 100644
--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/pgtable.h
@@ -1291,7 +1291,8 @@ static __always_inline void wrprotect_pte(struct folio *folio, unsigned long pf
 	} while (!try_cmpxchg((long *)&ptep->pte, (long *)&old_pte, *(long *)&new_pte));
 }

-#define flush_tlb_fix_spurious_fault(vma, address, ptep) do { } while (0)
+/* Force TLB flush for deterministic execution under hypervisors */
+#define flush_tlb_fix_spurious_fault(vma, address, ptep) flush_tlb_page(vma, address)

 #define  __HAVE_ARCH_PMDP_SET_ACCESS_FLAGS
 extern int pmdp_set_access_flags(struct vm_area_struct *vma,
--
2.39.0
